data.ground_truth:
The factors that the Internal Committee or Local Committee should consider when determining compensation for a woman who has been subjected to sexual harassment at workplace are as follows:
(a) mental trauma, pain, and suffering;
(b) loss of reputation;
(c) humiliation suffered;
(d) loss of earnings or benefits during the period she was harassed;
(e) any other relevant factors.

The committee should consider these factors in a manner that is fair, reasonable, and just to ensure that the compensation is adequate and proportional to the harm caused.

