data.ground_truth:
As per The Sexual Harassment of Women at Workplace (Prevention, Prohibition and Redressal) Act, 2013, while making a complaint under Section 9 of the Right to Information Act, 2005, you are required to submit specific documents. These documents include: 

* Identity and address proof of the aggrieved woman;
* Details of the alleged harasser(s);
* Timeframe and location where the incident occurred;
* Any previous complaints or incidents that may be relevant to the case;
* Recommendations of the Internal Committee or Local Committee, as the case may be.

Additionally, you may also need to provide information about any conciliation proceedings undertaken, inquiry reports, and actions taken by the employer or District Officer. It's essential to keep in mind that these documents will vary depending on your specific situation and context.

